  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN176.1-kilavi">tōḻi talaimakaṉai vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante refuses the door to HIM.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN176.1">
        <l>kaṭalkaṇ ṭaṉṉa kaṇṇakaṉ parappi</l>
        <l>ṉilampaka vīḻnta vērmutir kiḻaṅkiṟ</l>
        <l>kaḻaikaṇ ṭaṉṉa tūmpuṭait tiraḷkāṟ</l>
        <l>kaḷiṟṟuccevi yaṉṉa pācaṭai maruṅkiṟ</l>
        <l>kaḻunivan taṉṉa koḻumukai yiṭaiyiṭai</l>
        <l>muṟuva<supplied>ṉ</supplied> mukatti<supplied>ṟ</supplied> paṉmalar tayaṅkap</l>
        <l>pūtta tāmaraip puḷḷimiḻ paḻaṉattu</l>
        <l>vēppunaṉai yaṉṉa neṭuṅka ṇīrñeṇ</l>
        <l>ṭiraitēr veṇkuru kañci yayala</l>
        <l>tolinta pakaṉṟai yiruñcēṟ ṟaḷḷaṟ</l>
        <l>ṟitalaiyiṉ varippa vōṭi viraintutaṉ</l>
        <l>ṉīrmali maṇṇaḷaic ceṟiyu mūra</l>
        <l>maṉainaṭu vayalai maraṉivar koḻuṅkoṭi</l>
        <l>yarimala rāmpalō ṭārtaḻait taii</l>
        <l>viḻavāṭu makaḷiroṭu taḻuvaṇip polintu</l>
        <l>malarē ruṇkaṇ māṇiḻai muṉkaik</l>
        <l>kuṟuntoṭi tuṭakkiya neṭuntoṭar viṭutta</l>
        <l>tuṭaṉṟaṉaḷ pōluniṉ kātali yempōṟ</l>
        <l>pulluḷaik kuṭumip putalvarp payantu</l>
        <l>nelluṭai neṭunakar niṉṉiṉ ṟuṟaiya</l>
        <l>veṉṉa kaṭattaḷō maṟṟē taṉmukat</l>
        <l>teḻuteḻil citaiya vaḻutaṉa ḷēṅki</l>
        <l>yaṭitteṉa vurutta tittip pallūḻ</l>
        <l>noṭitteṉac civanta melviraṟ ṟirukupu</l>
        <l>kūrnuṉai maḻukiya veyiṟṟa</l>
        <l>ḷūrmuḻutu nuvaluniṟ kāṇiya ceṉmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Oh man from a village, (12d)</l>
        <l>where, in the tank buzzing with birds among the lotuses that bloom (7)</l>
        <l>so that many blossoms glitter like smiling faces (6)</l>
        <l>all amidst rich buds as if stakes had come up (5)</l>
        <l>among the green leaves that are like elephant ears (4)</l>
        <l>with hollow round stems that look like bamboo, (3)</l>
        <l>with tubers maturing in roots that descend to split the ground (2)</l>
        <l>on the surface of a wide area that looks like an ocean, (1)</l>
        <l>the moist crab with eyes long as the buds of the Neem tree (8)</l>
        <l>afraid of the white heron searching for prey hastily</l>
        <l>runs through the dark muddy mire with Jalap sprouted</l>
        <l>nearby, so as to leave traces like stretch marks, (9-11)</l>
        <l>[and] hides in its earth hole full of water, (12a-c)</l>
        <l>your lover is enraged, it seems, (18)</l>
        <l>at [your] letting go of a long connection in order to catch hold of the short bracelets (17)</l>
        <l>on the forearms of [her] with glorious jewels [and] flower-like kajal eyes, (16)</l>
        <l>decorations shining in the embrace with women dancing in the festival, (15)</l>
        <l>after having woven [an attire of] full foliage together with white waterlilies [and] blossoms cut (14)</l>
        <l>from the rich creeper climbing the Purslane tree planted by the house. (13)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">Like us, (18d)</l>
        <l>to bring forth sons with coarse-maned heads (19)</l>
        <l>[and] stay in the paddy-rich long mansion without you, (20)</l>
        <l>what duty does she have? (21a-c)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">About her crying</l>
        <l>so that the beauty painted in her face is ruined, lamenting, (21df.)</l>
        <l>with marks that formed because she slapped [her belly], (23a-c)</l>
        <l>wringing [her] soft fingers that turned red as she snapped them many times, (24)</l>
        <l>one with teeth whose sharp tips have become blunt [from gnashing], (25)</l>
        <l>the whole village talks, when they see you. Go! (26)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
